abstract: >-
  PyBurgers is a high-performance solver for the 1D Stochastic
  Burgers Equation that implements both Direct Numerical Simulation
  (DNS) and Large-Eddy Simulation (LES) capabilities. The solver
  uses Fourier collocation methods for spatial derivatives and
  Williamson (1980) low-storage RK3 time integration with CFL-based
  adaptive time stepping, following the procedures described in
  Basu (2009). It features four subgrid-scale turbulence models,
  FFTW-optimized FFT operations with intelligent wisdom caching,
  and fractional Brownian motion stochastic forcing.
